
*(manually) Partition the compact flash according to the RADL

*(manually) Get Hardware description from lynx:
.lsk_autoconfig_cmdsdata (called lynxHD below)

radler setps for lynx deployment use the lynxHD file as input and the CF as a connected device to
  checks lynxHD against the radl description (which check the CF partitioning)
  gets mapping between radl names and lynx names
  uses learned mapping to call the autoconfig tools
  'copy' the generated boot partitions / bootloader / hypervisor / ? fomr lynx
  dd each partition image
  mount the partitions
  write the required files (nodes, init process, startup scripts, shm linux kernels, firewall rules, ipsec config, network config, ...)

CF Ready to boot and run.


